Hi !
It's been a long time since I last used this project but I want to put my hands on it again. I was trying to get the last seen time of a number but I wasn't successful. 

To be honest, my plan was/is to use this PHP code to create a Java application to use WhatsApp. This way I will improve my Java skills and learn PHP ( and also how to link them in the same project ). 

First of all, I want to understand the code the best as I can but there are so many files, what developping application do you use to edit the whole project ? Do you use eclipse ? Can I import the whole code into a project in eclipse ? 

I think that's enough for now. Thanks in advanced !

Quiero crear una aplicación Java para ordenadores.

Ya intenté editar el código de *examples/whatsapp.php* y usar la función *sendGetRequestLastSeen* sin éxito. Necesito saber que pasos tengo que llevar a cabo para poder usar esa función. Supongo que primero habrá que conectarse, conseguir la contraseña para descifrar RC4 etc. para después poder ejecutar esa función, ¿ cierto ? ¿ Qué pasos son ? 

Aparte, después de usar esa función, ¿ a donde va la información que he solicitado ? No hay *return* ni nada similar, entonces, ¿ de donde leo la respuesta ?
___________________________________________________________________________

I want to create a Java app for computers.

I tryied to edit the code of *examples/whatsapp.php* and use the *sendGetRequestLastSeen* function unsuccessfully. I need to know what steps I have to follow in order to use that function. First of all, I suppose I need to connect to the servers, get the password to decrypt RC4 etc. so that I can execute the function, right ? ¿ What steps are they ?

Apart from that, after using that func, where is the info I requested ? There is no *return* so where do I read the data ?

sendGetRequestLastSeen, no es una función. Sino, un procedimiento. que envía una solicitud a whatsapp pidiendo la ultima actividad de X usuario.
Luego lo que retorna desde Whatsapp, se cuela desde la recepción de los mensajes. Pero en WhatsAPI hay eventos que ejecutan Procedimientos o Funciones enviandoles parámetros.

-----------------------------------
sendGetRequestLastSeen is not a function. Otherwise, a procedure. sending a request asking whatsapp last activity X user. 
After returning from the Whatsapp, strain from receiving messages. But WhatsAPI has events them running procedures or functions with parameters.
pollMessages pull from the socket, and place incoming messages in the message queue.

It's pollMessages dammit, POLL!

Yes, you need to call pollMessage or pollMessages to receive and process incoming data. That's one of the limitations of PHP, no multithreading stuff.

Here you go
https://github.com/venomous0x/WhatsAPI/blob/master/src/whatsprot.class.php#L2207
Wow, that *iq* tag really fooled me. I guess *messageQueue* is the variable I should check, right ?

\*sigh* yes you could use that legacy method

*OR*

you can do it the intended way by utilizing the event manager

Yep.

Boop https://github.com/shirioko/WhatsAPI/wiki/WhatsApi-events

Also as @sbalgas suggested I'd recommend using WhatsApiNet as a reference for Java instead of WhatsAPI
PHP has some flaws/features which don't translate too well to a lower language e.g. loose typing and single threading

Also WhatsApiNet is better maintained by me than WhatsAPI :')
@shirioko Okey, I'll gve it a try. Could you change the title of the thread to "How to get last seen" ? It could be useful for other users.
